Package: rmpd
Version: 0.5.0+native1
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: ibiscum <>
Installed-Size: 16651
Depends: libasound2t64 (>= 1.1.0), libc6 (>= 2.39), libchromaprint1 (>= 1.3.2), libgcc-s1 (>= 4.2), adduser
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/M0Rf30/rmpd
Description: modern Rust Music Player Daemon implementation
 rmpd is a modern, memory-safe music server written in Rust.
 It aims for high compatibility with the MPD protocol while adding
 native Rust extensibility, multi-output playback, MPRIS integration,
 and optional remote music sources.
 .
 This package installs the rmpd daemon, a systemd service unit,
 and a system-wide sample configuration at /etc/rmpd/rmpd.toml.
